<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,577,1584,1644]" box="[151,263,1620,1644]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,255,1620,1644]" captionStart="FIGURE 210" captionStartId="252.[151,244,2014,2035]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,1395,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-50@252.[176,1411,1391,1993]" captionTargetPageId="252" captionText="FIGURE 210. Rhotana truncata, holotype ♂." pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 210</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1436,1691,2004]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,296,1691,1716]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Forewings 2.0 times longer than wide, length about 
<quantity box="[881,969,1692,1716]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="mm" value="5.6">5.6 mm</quantity>
. Colour stramineous to light brown. Forewings not powdered, faintly infuscated, interrupted by clear areas, slightly darker in a mark distad of clavus apex and in a V-shaped band from last subcostal sector to base of Ms3 and to 2nd subcostal sector; a red mark around base of last subcostal sector and apex of Sc; 2nd subcostal sector and surrounding veins, apical margin, and anterior apical cross-veins and surrounding veins red; remaining veins stramineous. Hindwings with three brown-black marks around apices of Ms1, Ms2, and claval vein. Pygofer of male genitalia with a pair of prominent, lateral projections. Genital styles elongated, a small hump between dorsal processes. Aedeagus short, apical part truncated, without processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1131,1980,2004]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1436,1691,2004]" box="[199,1131,1980,2004]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
